    <p>SCRIB­BLE TOWN</p>
    <p>Scrib­ble Town ad­dresses the tough topic of bul­ly­ing in an ac­ces­si­ble fash­ion for kids aged be­tween nine and 12.</p>
    <p>Three char­ac­ters, Sam, Dan and Ly­dia, are Scrib­ble Town in­hab­i­tants who wake up one day to dis­cover that colour has dis­ap­peared from their town. They go on a quest to fix the Colour­wheel.</p>
    <p>Along the way, kids can an­swer in­ter­ac­tive quizzes for a bet­ter un­der­stand­ing of dif­fer­ent types of bul­ly­ing, how and why bul­ly­ing oc­curs and how it af­fects peo­ple.</p>
    <p>WHERE Sun Yat Sen Nanyang Memo­rial Hall,</p>
    <p>12 Tai Gin Road MRT Novena</p>
    <p>WHEN Till Jan 31, Tues­days to Sun­days, 10am to 5pm AD­MIS­SION Free for Sin­ga­pore­ans and per­ma­nent res­i­dents</p>
    <p>INFO str.sg/JEGN</p>

